  "text": "When studying CNV-associated human diseases, accurate and efficient CNV genotyping is one of the key steps. Many techniques have been widely applied in CNV studies, such as fluorescence in situ hybridization, comparative genomic hybridization arrays (CGH), quantitative realtime PCR, and multiplex ligation-dependent probe amplification (MLPA). These assays rely on either arrayor PCR-based methods and offer different degrees of resolution, precision, and throughput [CITATION_1] . All methods have advantages and limitations in different settings.",
